              <td>
			  <!-- inclue current newsletter here. --->
			 
			  June 2004<br>
<br>
In this issue:
<p>1. The SimpleNet Site of the Month!<br>
  2. Our Partner: JimWorld Johnny&#8217;s Ramblings<br>
  3. What&#8217;s Cool this Month?<br>
  4. Why SimpleNet? Optimal Traffic Routing, and why you need it!<br>
  5. The SimpleNet Referral Program<br>
  6. Send Us Feedback!</p>
<p>---------------------------------------------------------<br>
  1. SimpleNet Site of the Month: June 2004<br>
  <a href="http://www.mojothemighty.com"><br>
  http://www.mojothemighty.com</a></p>
<p>The Adventures of MOJO THE MIGHTY are captured in this charmingly fun web
  site. The web site was initially created as a way to share pictures of the
  canine, MOJO. But, it has begun to take on a life of its own as MOJO continues
  his adventures. Check it out!</p>
<p>To check out the Site of the Month, please visit:<br>
  <a href="http://www.simplenet.com/som">http://www.simplenet.com/som</a></p>
<p>How does my site become the Site of the Month?<br>
  Simply visit our Site of the Month page and add your site to the list of sites
    to be reviewed, read the terms and sign up! To sign up now:<br>
    <a href="http://www.simplenet.com/som">http://www.simplenet.com/som</a></p>
<p>---------------------------------------------------------<br>
  2. JimWorld: A Resource for Web Site Owners<br>
  An excerpt from the JimWorld Gazette&#8230;</p>
<p>In Johnny&#8217;s Crosshairs&#8230;<br>
  One question has been the minds of SEO forum members across the Internet, what
    the heck is going on in Mountain View?? Webmasters and professional SEOs
    have gotten used to watching and noting changes to the Google algorithm over
    the past several years. After all, this is how search engines like Google
    improve themselves. Sometimes, Google updates trump all previous updates
    and cause the industry to go haywire. Conjecture, accusations and theories
    start flying around message boards and discussion lists around the Web&#8230; read
    more at the Gazette!</p>
<p>For more tips on SEO optimization and other resources, please visit our partner,
  JimWorld. Archives of their newsletter can be found online at:<br>
  <a href="http://jimworld.com/gazette/issue-208/">http://jimworld.com/gazette/issue-208/</a></p>
<p>---------------------------------------------------------<br>
  4. What&#8217;s Cool on the &#8216;Net this Month?</p>
<p>We, at SimpleNet, spend all day on the &#8216;net, so why wouldn&#8217;t we
  tell you about some of the crazy stuff that we encounter? Well, here ya go!
  Each month we&#8217;ll show you something that we&#8217;ve found that we think
  is totally cool. Enjoy!</p>
<p>The flash animation is amazing, and the game is dang fun, too!<br>
  <a href="http://analogik.org/samorost.a">http://analogik.org/samorost.asp</a></p>
<p>---------------------------------------------------------<br>
  4. Why SimpleNet? Optimal Traffic Routing, and why you need it!</p>
<p>On the Internet, transmission rates, error rates, BGP, route flaps, and other
  characteristics can be measured, improved, and, to some extent, guaranteed
  in advance. How does this affect your web site? Your host&#8217;s network should
  be able to decipher this information and send traffic from your web site to
  your customers along the most optimal route. This assures that your customers
  are receiving your product or service information swiftly and without loss.<br>
    <br>
    Much like when driving your car, there are several streets that you can take
    to get to your desired destination. Sometimes you will encounter construction
    or an accident that will require you to take an alternative street. Not only
    does SimpleNet go out of its way to make sure that your site is reliable
    and secure, but we also make sure that your site can serve its visitors as
    efficiently as possible by finely tuning BGP routes, connecting to multiple
    major Internet backbones, and statistically analyzing traffic for performance
    adjustments. If you are concerned about providing a quality experience, you
    must ensure that your visitors can fly through your site!</p>
<p>Our optimal, redundant, reliable, and revolutionary web hosting platform is
  the only home for your site.</p>
<p>---------------------------------------------------------<br>
  5. The SimpleNet Referral Program</p>
<p>The SimpleNet Referral Program allows you to earn credit towards you current
  account balance by referring your family, friends, and associates to SimpleNet.
  For each new web site account that is referred to us, you will receive one
  FREE month of service on your existing account (up to $35)! The more new accounts
  that you refer, the more FREE months you will receive.</p>
<p>To learn more about the Referral Program, please visit:<br>
  <a href="http://simplenet.com/referral.html">http://simplenet.com/referral.html</a></p>
<p>---------------------------------------------------------<br>
6. We want to hear from you!</p>
<p>The best way for us to bring you the services that you need is for you to
  tell us what you want! Whether it be to talk about our support, suggest new
  services or just tell us that we are doing a great job, please use our feedback
  areas as often as you like!</p>
<p>How do you do that?<br>
  1. Reply to this email<br>
  OR<br>
  2. Use our feedback form, located at:<br>
  <a href="http://www.simplenet.com/contact.html">http://www.simplenet.com/contact.html</a></p>
<p>---------------------------------------------------------</p>
<p>Thanks for reading and for being a SimpleNet customer!</p>
<p>Best wishes,<br>
  The SimpleNet Team</p>
<p>For assistance, please contact Customer Service:<br>
  <a href="http://simplenet.com/contact.html">http://simplenet.com/contact.html</a></p>
<p>SimpleNet takes your privacy seriously. To learn more,<br>
  please read our privacy policy, located at<br>
  <a href="http://www.simplenet.com/privacy.html">http://www.simplenet.com/privacy.html</a><br>
</p>
			  
